This is one of the Christian mysteries —perhaps, if we could realise it, the hardest to overleap by faith; for if Jesus was merely human, and feebly inspired at that, this is precisely what we should have expected him to do. Incapacity to understand the difficulties and see the virtues of his opponents is the heritage of every common reformer.
